## Current scope

This starter now includes live market-data retrieval through Alpaca or `yfinance`,
while the research and sentiment layers remain otherwise lightweight.

- `LiveMarketDataTool`
- `NewsSentimentTool`
- `LiveOptionsChainTool`
- `PortfolioStateTool`
- `BacktestTool`
- `MarketResearchTool`
- `TechnicalIndicatorTool`
- `OptionsStrategyTool`
- `RiskBudgetTool`
- `ExecutionPlanTool`

## Setup

```bash
python -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e .[dev]
cp .env.example .env
```

Add your LLM provider key to `.env` so CrewAI can run.

## Run

```bash
python -m crewai_github_template.main \
  --ticker NVDA \
  --thesis "AI demand stays strong into the next earnings print" \
  --macro-view "Growth remains favored while rates stabilize" \
  --upcoming-event "Quarterly earnings" \
  --price 910 \
  --rsi 61 \
  --macd-signal bullish \
  --moving-average-gap-pct 4.8 \
  --bollinger-position upper \
  --news-sentiment 0.35 \
  --social-sentiment 0.20 \
  --analyst-revision-trend up \
  --implied-volatility-pct 38 \
  --days-to-expiry 21 \
  --portfolio-value 100000 \
  --max-position-pct 5 \
  --stop-loss-pct 4 \
  --conviction 0.70 \
  --execution-mode paper \
  --broker Alpaca \
  --order-type market \
  --time-in-force day
```

The final memo is written to `output/trade_decision.md`.

If `MARKET_DATA_PROVIDER=alpaca`, the tool will try Alpaca first and automatically
fall back to `yfinance` when Alpaca data is unavailable. Set
`MARKET_DATA_PROVIDER=yfinance` if you want to force read-only fallback data.

The manager now also receives:
- live news sentiment
- live options-chain context
- Alpaca account and positions state
- a simple historical backtest

Execution safety controls:
- `ALPACA_KILL_SWITCH=true` blocks all submissions
- `ALPACA_ALLOW_EXTENDED_HOURS=false` blocks submissions outside regular market hours
- duplicate open orders with the same ticker, side, and share count are blocked

## Next build phases

1. Replace the local research and sentiment placeholders with real market/news data tools.
2. Add historical data ingestion and backtests.
3. Add paper trading through Alpaca or another broker API.
4. Add portfolio state, PnL tracking, and exposure controls.

